FT  20 OCT 94 / Brescia steel aid approved
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   BRUSSELS
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
The European Commission has approved an Italian government aid package to
help steelmakers in the Brescia region restructure. The Commission said in a
statement the Ecu410m (Pounds 323m) plan would add 5m tonnes in capacity
cuts to the 11m already achieved as part of an EU-wide rescue package for
the European steel industry. The EU has demanded 19m tonnes of capacity cuts
by November 8 for the overall package to go ahead. The Commission said the
Italian plan involved L600bn in aid to help close down steel mills in the
Brescia region and L190m to help re-employ redundant workers. The Italian
plan is a revamped version of a package earlier deemed by the EU to breach
its aid rules.
