<HEADLINE>
FT  19 OCT 94 / World Stock Markets: Brazil improves 2.6%
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Shares in Sao Paulo finished 2.6 per cent ahead after moderate trade,
boosted by a new influx of foreign money into the market as bargain hunting
took place. The Bovespa index improved 1,252 to 49,096, but in spite of the
rally, stocks were still down 10.5 per cent over the month to date. Volume
was RDollars 313.4m (Dollars 370.4m).
Analysts said the end of a struggle between shorts and longs seen prior to
the futures settlements on October 13 and 17 eased the downward pressure on
prices. But they remained concerned about the impact of rising inflation on
the government's anti-inflation plan. The market upward revised its October
inflation forecasts to around 3.0 per cent after 0.8 per cent inflation in
September. It was feared that the government would lift interest rates in
the short term in an effort to contain a recent consumer surge in spending
and hold prices down.
</TEXT>
<XX>
Countries:-
</XX>
<CN>BRZ  Brazil, South America.
</CN>
