Taiwan Cement, the country's biggest cement manufacturer, has reported
pre-tax profits of TDollars 2.37bn (USDollars 90.6m) for the first nine
months of the year, down sharply from TDollars 3.36bn a year earlier, writes
Laura Tyson in Taipei. The company, controlled by the Koo family, said the
