Turnover also fell, to TDollars 13.44bn from TDollars 15.04bn, in part due
to a slowdown in public and private construction.
Imports of Japanese cement at 'unreasonably low' prices had pushed domestic
prices down 5 per cent since the beginning of the year, the company said.
About 90 per cent of Taiwan's cement imports come from Japan.
