FT  19 OCT 94 / The Lex Column: Rolling contracts
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Mr Tom Buffett's five-year rolling contract at Automated Security Holdings
provides a good test for the whole 'roller' concept. This is a case of
manifest failure: ASH's share price has underperformed the market by 77 per
cent since the start of 1990. Defenders of rollers say they do not
necessarily reward failure as boards can insist on a reduced pay-off if
performance is poor. ASH now has the chance to show whether that is so.
