</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   BANGKOK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Italian-Thai Development, Thailand's largest construction company, confirmed
yesterday it had signed a memorandum of understanding with the Philippines
government for a Dollars 3bn project to turn the former US Clark airbase
north of Manila into an international airport. The project would be a
'build-operate-transfer' scheme to convert the airbase into a passenger and
cargo airport with an aircraft maintenance centre by the end of 1997; to
develop a 'mass transit' railway system from Clark to Makati, the Metro
Manila business district, and on southwards to the industrial zone
south-east of the capital; and to expand and improve road links to Clark.
It is not clear, however, how the plan to redevelop Clark will fit in with a
similar and further advanced project for nearby Subic Bay, the former US
naval base, which also has a big airport.
