This was far worse than even the most pessimistic London analyst had
expected and the company now has very few friends in the City. UBS
reiterated a sell notice which has been in place for a record-breaking seven
years.
Few houses had any clear idea of where Eurotunnel's trading patterns go from
here. The general consensus was that if another immediate cash call has been
avoided there could yet be painful decisions early in the new year.
