<HEADLINE>
FT  18 OCT 94 / World Stock Markets: Mexico
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Equities finished mildly easier after investors shadowed the movements of
Mexican blue chips traded on Wall Street. The IPC index shed 21.72 or 0.78
per cent to 2,755.97. Turnover totalled a light 518.3m new pesos on 37.4m
shares traded.
Brokers said they expected stocks to make gains during the week in
anticipation of a flow of third-quarter results before the month's end. The
market had risen 6 per cent in the previous four sessions.
