<TEXT>
Strength in gold and other metal shares was not enough to keep the Toronto
market from posting a slight loss in moderate trading. The TSE 300 index
ended 5.4 easier at 4,327.0 and declines led rises by 415 to 308. Volume was
45.2m shares valued at CDollars 600m.
Remarks by the federal finance minister Mr Paul Martin reiterating the
government's commitment to tackling the country's deficit problem lent some
strength to the Canadian dollar.
